@page "/components/border-beam"
@using RizzyUI

<PageTitle>Border Beam</PageTitle>

<RzQuickReferenceContainer>
    <RzArticle ProseWidth="ProseWidth.UltraWide">
        <SideContent>
            <RzQuickReference />
        </SideContent>
        <MainContent>
            <RzBreadcrumb class="mb-4 not-prose">
                <BreadcrumbList>
                    <BreadcrumbItem>
                        <BreadcrumbLink Href="/" hx-boost="true" hx-select="#content" hx-target="#content" hx-swap="outerHTML">Docs</BreadcrumbLink>
                    </BreadcrumbItem>
                    <BreadcrumbSeparator />
                    <BreadcrumbItem>
                        <BreadcrumbLink Href="/components" hx-boost="true" hx-select="#content" hx-target="#content" hx-swap="outerHTML">Components</BreadcrumbLink>
                    </BreadcrumbItem>
                    <BreadcrumbSeparator />
                    <BreadcrumbItem>
                        <BreadcrumbPage>Border Beam</BreadcrumbPage>
                    </BreadcrumbItem>
                </BreadcrumbList>
            </RzBreadcrumb>

            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H1" QuickReferenceTitle="Border Beam" class="scroll-mt-20">Border Beam</RzHeading>
            <RzParagraph>
                <code>RzBorderBeam</code> is a decorative overlay for cards, buttons, and panels that animates a gradient beam around a border.
                It is a single SSR-only presentational component driven by CSS animation and works best when the host uses
                <code>relative overflow-hidden</code> with a visible corner radius.
            </RzParagraph>

            <RzAlert Variant="ThemeVariant.Information" class="my-5">
                <AlertTitle>Under the Hood</AlertTitle>
                <AlertDescription>
                    <code>RzBorderBeam</code> renders no interactive behavior. The effect comes from CSS masking and motion-path animation
                    rather than Blazor interactivity. Hosts should generally use <code>relative overflow-hidden</code> (and rounded corners when desired).
                </AlertDescription>
            </RzAlert>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Basic Usage" class="scroll-mt-20">Basic Usage</RzHeading>
                <RzParagraph>Use a relatively positioned and clipped host, then place <code>RzBorderBeam</code> as a child.</RzParagraph>
                <RzBrowser Layout="typeof(PreviewLayout)">
                    <div class="mx-auto max-w-md p-8">
                        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Border Beam Card</RzHeading>
                            <RzParagraph class="mt-2">Decorative perimeter animation for static content.</RzParagraph>
                            <RzBorderBeam />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </RzBrowser>
                <RzCodeViewer Language="@CodeLanguage.Razor" class="mb-10">
&lt;div class=&quot;relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6&quot;&gt;
    &lt;RzHeading Level=&quot;HeadingLevel.H4&quot;&gt;Border Beam Card&lt;/RzHeading&gt;
    &lt;RzParagraph class=&quot;mt-2&quot;&gt;Decorative perimeter animation for static content.&lt;/RzParagraph&gt;
    &lt;RzBorderBeam /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
                </RzCodeViewer>
            </section>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Custom Colors and Thickness" class="scroll-mt-20">Custom Colors and Thickness</RzHeading>
                <RzParagraph>
                    Tune the gradient and border weight using <code>ColorFrom</code>, <code>ColorTo</code>, <code>BorderWidth</code>, and <code>BeamClass</code>.
                    Root <code>class</code> attributes apply to the overlay root, while <code>BeamClass</code> targets the moving beam element.
                </RzParagraph>
                <RzBrowser Layout="typeof(PreviewLayout)">
                    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-3xl gap-4 p-8 md:grid-cols-2">
                        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Warm Accent</RzHeading>
                            <RzBorderBeam BorderWidth="2" ColorFrom="#ff8a00" ColorTo="#ff3d81" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Cool Accent</RzHeading>
                            <RzBorderBeam BorderWidth="3" ColorFrom="#22d3ee" ColorTo="#2563eb" BeamClass="opacity-90" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </RzBrowser>
                <RzCodeViewer Language="@CodeLanguage.Razor" class="mb-10">
&lt;RzBorderBeam BorderWidth=&quot;2&quot; ColorFrom=&quot;#ff8a00&quot; ColorTo=&quot;#ff3d81&quot; /&gt;
&lt;RzBorderBeam BorderWidth=&quot;3&quot; ColorFrom=&quot;#22d3ee&quot; ColorTo=&quot;#2563eb&quot; BeamClass=&quot;opacity-90&quot; /&gt;
                </RzCodeViewer>
            </section>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Reverse Direction and Timing" class="scroll-mt-20">Reverse Direction and Timing</RzHeading>
                <RzParagraph>
                    Configure motion using <code>Reverse</code>, <code>Duration</code>, <code>Delay</code>, and <code>InitialOffset</code>.
                    Delay is rendered as an already-in-progress animation offset to match the original MagicUI feel.
                </RzParagraph>
                <RzBrowser Layout="typeof(PreviewLayout)">
                    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-3xl gap-4 p-8 md:grid-cols-2">
                        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Default Direction</RzHeading>
                            <RzBorderBeam Duration="8" Delay="1.5" InitialOffset="15" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Reverse Direction</RzHeading>
                            <RzBorderBeam Duration="4" Reverse="true" Delay="0.75" InitialOffset="35" ColorFrom="#34d399" ColorTo="#10b981" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </RzBrowser>
                <RzCodeViewer Language="@CodeLanguage.Razor" class="mb-10">
&lt;RzBorderBeam Duration=&quot;8&quot; Delay=&quot;1.5&quot; InitialOffset=&quot;15&quot; /&gt;
&lt;RzBorderBeam Duration=&quot;4&quot; Reverse=&quot;true&quot; Delay=&quot;0.75&quot; InitialOffset=&quot;35&quot; ColorFrom=&quot;#34d399&quot; ColorTo=&quot;#10b981&quot; /&gt;
                </RzCodeViewer>
            </section>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Button Integration" class="scroll-mt-20">Button Integration</RzHeading>
                <RzParagraph>
                    Border Beam can be layered inside a button-style host. Keep visible focus styles on the host so the decorative beam does not replace focus affordance.
                </RzParagraph>
                <RzBrowser Layout="typeof(PreviewLayout)">
                    <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-md justify-center p-8">
                        <button class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-lg border px-8 py-3 font-medium shadow-sm focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
                            Buy Now
                            <RzBorderBeam Size="40" InitialOffset="20" ColorFrom="#fef08a" ColorTo="#eab308" />
                        </button>
                    </div>
                </RzBrowser>
                <RzCodeViewer Language="@CodeLanguage.Razor" class="mb-10">
&lt;button class=&quot;relative overflow-hidden rounded-lg border px-8 py-3 font-medium focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2&quot;&gt;
    Buy Now
    &lt;RzBorderBeam Size=&quot;40&quot; InitialOffset=&quot;20&quot; ColorFrom=&quot;#fef08a&quot; ColorTo=&quot;#eab308&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
                </RzCodeViewer>
            </section>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Multi-Beam Composition" class="scroll-mt-20">Multi-Beam Composition</RzHeading>
                <RzParagraph>
                    Layer multiple <code>RzBorderBeam</code> instances to create richer effects. Keep beam count modest for best rendering performance.
                </RzParagraph>
                <RzBrowser Layout="typeof(PreviewLayout)">
                    <div class="mx-auto max-w-lg p-8">
                        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Now Playing</RzHeading>
                            <RzParagraph class="mt-2">Stacked beams with distinct colors and delays.</RzParagraph>
                            <RzBorderBeam Size="280" Duration="6" ColorFrom="#fb7185" ColorTo="#ef4444" BeamClass="from-transparent via-red-500 to-transparent" />
                            <RzBorderBeam Size="280" Duration="6" Delay="3" BorderWidth="2" ColorFrom="#60a5fa" ColorTo="#3b82f6" BeamClass="from-transparent via-blue-500 to-transparent" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </RzBrowser>
                <RzCodeViewer Language="@CodeLanguage.Razor" class="mb-10">
&lt;div class=&quot;relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6&quot;&gt;
    &lt;RzBorderBeam Size=&quot;280&quot; Duration=&quot;6&quot; ColorFrom=&quot;#fb7185&quot; ColorTo=&quot;#ef4444&quot; BeamClass=&quot;from-transparent via-red-500 to-transparent&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;RzBorderBeam Size=&quot;280&quot; Duration=&quot;6&quot; Delay=&quot;3&quot; BorderWidth=&quot;2&quot; ColorFrom=&quot;#60a5fa&quot; ColorTo=&quot;#3b82f6&quot; BeamClass=&quot;from-transparent via-blue-500 to-transparent&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
                </RzCodeViewer>
            </section>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Edge Cases and Host Requirements" class="scroll-mt-20">Edge Cases and Host Requirements</RzHeading>
                <RzAlert Variant="ThemeVariant.Warning" class="my-4 not-prose">
                    <AlertTitle>Host Setup Matters</AlertTitle>
                    <AlertDescription>
                        The left sample intentionally omits <code>overflow-hidden</code> to show how the beam can spill outside the host. The right sample uses the recommended setup.
                    </AlertDescription>
                </RzAlert>
                <RzBrowser Layout="typeof(PreviewLayout)">
                    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-3xl gap-4 p-8 md:grid-cols-2">
                        <div class="relative rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Missing Overflow Clip</RzHeading>
                            <RzBorderBeam Size="120" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6">
                            <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H4">Recommended Host</RzHeading>
                            <RzBorderBeam Size="120" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </RzBrowser>
                <RzCodeViewer Language="@CodeLanguage.Razor" class="mb-10">
&lt;div class=&quot;relative rounded-xl border bg-card p-6&quot;&gt;
    &lt;RzBorderBeam Size=&quot;120&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border bg-card p-6&quot;&gt;
    &lt;RzBorderBeam Size=&quot;120&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
                </RzCodeViewer>
            </section>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Component Parameters" class="scroll-mt-20">Component Parameters</RzHeading>
                <div class="not-prose mt-6 mb-10 overflow-hidden rounded-md border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800"><table class="w-full text-sm"><thead class="text-left bg-zinc-100/75 font-semibold text-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900/50 dark:text-zinc-300"><tr><th scope="col" class="w-1/5 px-4 py-3">Property</th><th scope="col" class="w-2/5 px-4 py-3">Description</th><th scope="col" class="w-1/5 px-4 py-3">Type</th><th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3">Default</th></tr></thead><tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-200 dark:divide-zinc-800">
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>Size</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Beam square width/height in pixels.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>double</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>50</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>Duration</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Seconds for one perimeter cycle.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>double</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>6</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>Delay</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Animation delay in seconds (rendered as already in progress).</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>double</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>0</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>ColorFrom</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Gradient start color.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>string?</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>"#ffaa40"</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>ColorTo</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Gradient middle color.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>string?</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>"#9c40ff"</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>Reverse</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Reverses beam traversal direction.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>bool</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>false</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>InitialOffset</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Initial perimeter progress percentage.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>double</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>0</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>BorderWidth</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Mask border thickness in pixels.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>double</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>1</code></td></tr>
                    <tr class="align-top"><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>BeamClass</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4">Extra classes applied only to the moving beam element.</td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>string?</code></td><td class="px-4 py-4"><code>null</code></td></tr>
                </tbody></table></div>
            </section>

            <section class="my-8 py-2">
                <RzHeading Level="HeadingLevel.H2" QuickReferenceTitle="Alpine and Events" class="scroll-mt-20">Alpine and Events</RzHeading>
                <RzParagraph>No Alpine API. <code>RzBorderBeam</code> is CSS-driven, decorative, and emits no HTMX or Alpine events.</RzParagraph>
            </section>
        </MainContent>
    </RzArticle>
</RzQuickReferenceContainer>
